\b
\c 4
\p 
\v 1 King \w Nebuchadnezzar|strong="H5020"\w*, \w to|strong="H1934"\w* people \w of|strong="H1005"\w* every nation \w and|strong="H1005"\w* language \w in|strong="H1965"\w* \w the|strong="H5020"\w* whole world: I wish you well!\f + \fr 4:1 \ft “I wish you well”: literally, “May your ‘shelam’ increase.” “Shelam” in Aramaic is equivalent to the Hebrew “Shalom” and can mean both peace and prosperity. However, this is a standard letter greeting, and its use is really a stylized formula.\f*
\v 2 \w It|strong="H5922"\w* \w is|strong="H2493"\w* \w my|strong="H5922"\w* pleasure \w to|strong="H5922"\w* share \w with|strong="H5922"\w* \w you|strong="H5922"\w* \w an|strong="H2370"\w* \w account|strong="H5922"\w* \w of|strong="H5922"\w* \w the|strong="H5922"\w* signs \w and|strong="H1763"\w* wonders \w the|strong="H5922"\w* Most High God has done \w for|strong="H5922"\w* \w me|strong="H5922"\w*.
\p 
\v 3 \w His|strong="H6925"\w* signs \w are|strong="H1768"\w* incredible. \w His|strong="H6925"\w* wonders \w are|strong="H1768"\w* amazing! \w His|strong="H6925"\w* kingdom \w is|strong="H1768"\w* \w an|strong="H3606"\w* eternal kingdom, \w and|strong="H2493"\w* \w his|strong="H6925"\w* rule \w will|strong="H1768"\w* last \w for|strong="H1768"\w* \w all|strong="H3606"\w* generations!
\p 
\v 4 I, Nebuchadnezzar, was doing well at home, living happily \w in|strong="H5954"\w* my palace.
\v 5 \w But|strong="H1768"\w* \w then|strong="H1768"\w* \w one|strong="H6922"\w* night \w I|strong="H1768"\w* \w had|strong="H1768"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w dream|strong="H2493"\w* \w that|strong="H1768"\w* really scared \w me|strong="H6925"\w*—\w I|strong="H1768"\w* saw visions \w that|strong="H1768"\w* terrified \w me|strong="H6925"\w* \w while|strong="H5705"\w* \w I|strong="H1768"\w* lay \w in|strong="H5954"\w* \w my|strong="H1768"\w* bed.
\v 6 \w So|strong="H1768"\w* \w I|strong="H1768"\w* ordered \w all|strong="H3606"\w* \w the|strong="H3606"\w* wise men \w of|strong="H1768"\w* Babylon brought before me \w to|strong="H3046"\w* explain \w the|strong="H3606"\w* \w dream|strong="H2493"\w* \w to|strong="H3046"\w* me.
\v 7 When \w the|strong="H5922"\w* magicians, enchanters, astrologers, \w and|strong="H1934"\w* diviners came \w in|strong="H5922"\w* I told \w them|strong="H5922"\w* \w the|strong="H5922"\w* dream, but they couldn't explain \w to|strong="H5922"\w* \w me|strong="H5922"\w* what \w it|strong="H5922"\w* meant.
\v 8 \w In|strong="H8631"\w* \w the|strong="H3606"\w* \w end|strong="H5491"\w* Daniel \w came|strong="H4291"\w* before me \w and|strong="H8065"\w* I told him \w the|strong="H3606"\w* dream. (He \w is|strong="H3606"\w* also called Belteshazzar after my god, \w and|strong="H8065"\w* he \w has|strong="H8065"\w* \w the|strong="H3606"\w* spirit \w of|strong="H3606"\w* \w the|strong="H3606"\w* holy gods\f + \fr 4:8 \ft “Spirit of the holy gods”: or, “spirit of the holy God.” Nebuchadnezzar clearly vacillated in his “god concepts”—one moment identifying the true God as the only one, while at other times referring to a pagan god as “his god.” Also verses 9 and 18; and \xt 5:11\xt*\ft and \xt 5:14\xt*\ft .\f* \w in|strong="H8631"\w* him.)
\p 
\v 9 “Belteshazzar, chief \w of|strong="H4481"\w* magicians,” \w I|strong="H4481"\w* said,\f + \fr 4:9 \ft Implied.\f* “\w I|strong="H4481"\w* certainly know \w that|strong="H3606"\w* \w the|strong="H3606"\w* spirit \w of|strong="H4481"\w* \w the|strong="H3606"\w* holy gods \w is|strong="H3606"\w* \w in|strong="H1753"\w* \w you|strong="H4481"\w* \w and|strong="H8065"\w* \w that|strong="H3606"\w* \w no|strong="H3606"\w* mystery \w is|strong="H3606"\w* difficult \w for|strong="H4203"\w* \w you|strong="H4481"\w* \w to|strong="H4481"\w* explain. \w So|strong="H4481"\w* tell \w me|strong="H4481"\w* about what \w I|strong="H4481"\w* saw \w in|strong="H1753"\w* \w my|strong="H4481"\w* dream \w and|strong="H8065"\w* explain what \w it|strong="H8460"\w* means.
\p 
\v 10 As \w I|strong="H4481"\w* lay \w in|strong="H5922"\w* \w bed|strong="H4903"\w* dreaming, \w I|strong="H4481"\w* \w saw|strong="H2370"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* tree \w in|strong="H5922"\w* \w the|strong="H5922"\w* middle \w of|strong="H4481"\w* \w the|strong="H5922"\w* earth—\w a|strong="H3068"\w* really large tree.
\v 11 \w It|strong="H4481"\w* grew strong \w and|strong="H3652"\w* tall, reaching high into \w the|strong="H4481"\w* sky \w so|strong="H4481"\w* \w it|strong="H4481"\w* could be seen \w by|strong="H4481"\w* everyone in \w the|strong="H4481"\w* whole world.
\v 12 Its leaves \w were|strong="H1768"\w* beautiful, \w and|strong="H6523"\w* it \w was|strong="H2423"\w* full \w of|strong="H2920"\w* fruit \w for|strong="H1768"\w* all \w to|strong="H5974"\w* eat. \w Wild|strong="H1251"\w* \w animals|strong="H2423"\w* rested \w in|strong="H2508"\w* its shade, \w and|strong="H6523"\w* birds nested \w in|strong="H2508"\w* its branches. It fed all living creatures.
\p 
\v 13 As \w I|strong="H4481"\w* went \w on|strong="H5922"\w* dreaming, lying \w on|strong="H5922"\w* \w my|strong="H5922"\w* bed, \w I|strong="H4481"\w* saw \w a|strong="H3068"\w* watcher, \w a|strong="H3068"\w* holy one,\f + \fr 4:13 \ft “A watcher, a holy one”: this is usually understood to be an angel.\f* coming down \w from|strong="H4481"\w* heaven.
\v 14 \w He|strong="H1768"\w* cried \w out|strong="H6966"\w* \w in|strong="H5922"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* loud voice, ‘Cut down \w the|strong="H5922"\w* tree \w and|strong="H4437"\w* chop off \w its|strong="H3046"\w* branches! Shake off \w its|strong="H3046"\w* leaves \w and|strong="H4437"\w* scatter \w its|strong="H3046"\w* fruit! Drive \w the|strong="H5922"\w* animals away \w from|strong="H1768"\w* \w its|strong="H3046"\w* shade, \w and|strong="H4437"\w* scare off \w the|strong="H5922"\w* birds \w from|strong="H1768"\w* \w its|strong="H3046"\w* branches.
\v 15 \w But|strong="H3606"\w* leave \w the|strong="H3606"\w* stump \w and|strong="H4430"\w* \w its|strong="H6591"\w* roots \w in|strong="H5020"\w* \w the|strong="H3606"\w* ground, \w and|strong="H4430"\w* bind it \w with|strong="H6903"\w* iron \w and|strong="H4430"\w* bronze, surrounded by \w the|strong="H3606"\w* new grass \w of|strong="H4437"\w* \w the|strong="H3606"\w* field. Let him\f + \fr 4:15 \ft “Him”: there is a gradual transition from the actual image of the tree to its application to King Nebuchadnezzar.\f* become soaked \w with|strong="H6903"\w* \w the|strong="H3606"\w* dew \w of|strong="H4437"\w* heaven, \w and|strong="H4430"\w* let him live \w with|strong="H6903"\w* \w the|strong="H3606"\w* animals outside \w in|strong="H5020"\w* \w the|strong="H3606"\w* undergrowth.
\v 16 Let \w his|strong="H1768"\w* mind become like \w that|strong="H1768"\w* \w of|strong="H4430"\w* \w an|strong="H4430"\w* animal. Let him \w be|strong="H8160"\w* like this \w for|strong="H1768"\w* \w seven|strong="H2298"\w* \w times|strong="H2298"\w*.\f + \fr 4:16 \ft The most common interpretation of “times” is “years,” and this is the understanding of the Septuagint, Josephus, and traditional Jewish commentators.\f*
\v 17 \w This|strong="H3606"\w* \w is|strong="H1768"\w* \w the|strong="H3606"\w* decree conveyed by \w the|strong="H3606"\w* watchers, \w the|strong="H3606"\w* verdict declared by \w the|strong="H3606"\w* holy ones \w in|strong="H8631"\w* order \w that|strong="H1768"\w* \w everyone|strong="H3606"\w* alive may know \w that|strong="H1768"\w* \w the|strong="H3606"\w* Most High rules over human kingdoms. \w He|strong="H1768"\w* gives them \w to|strong="H8065"\w* \w anyone|strong="H3606"\w* \w he|strong="H1768"\w* chooses—\w he|strong="H1768"\w* puts \w the|strong="H3606"\w* most humble individuals \w in|strong="H8631"\w* charge.’
\p 
\v 18 \w This|strong="H3606"\w* \w is|strong="H3606"\w* what I, King Nebuchadnezzar, saw \w in|strong="H1753"\w* my dream. Now \w it|strong="H8460"\w*'s up \w to|strong="H8065"\w* you, Belteshazzar, \w to|strong="H8065"\w* give me \w the|strong="H3606"\w* explanation \w as|strong="H3606"\w* you have before. \w None|strong="H3606"\w* \w of|strong="H1753"\w* \w the|strong="H3606"\w* wise men \w in|strong="H1753"\w* my kingdom could explain \w it|strong="H8460"\w* \w to|strong="H8065"\w* me. \w But|strong="H3606"\w* you can, \w because|strong="H3606"\w* \w the|strong="H3606"\w* spirit \w of|strong="H1753"\w* \w the|strong="H3606"\w* holy gods \w is|strong="H3606"\w* \w in|strong="H1753"\w* you.”
\p 
\v 19 \w When|strong="H1768"\w* Daniel (\w also|strong="H4430"\w* called Belteshazzar) heard this, \w he|strong="H1768"\w* \w was|strong="H4430"\w* upset \w for|strong="H1768"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* while, disturbed \w as|strong="H1768"\w* \w he|strong="H1768"\w* thought about it. \w The|strong="H1768"\w* \w king|strong="H4430"\w* told him, “Belteshazzar, don't be worried about \w the|strong="H1768"\w* dream \w and|strong="H4430"\w* \w what|strong="H1768"\w* it means.”
\p “\w My|strong="H1768"\w* lord, \w I|strong="H1768"\w* only wish this dream \w was|strong="H4430"\w* \w for|strong="H1768"\w* \w those|strong="H1768"\w* \w who|strong="H1768"\w* hate \w you|strong="H1768"\w* \w and|strong="H4430"\w* \w the|strong="H1768"\w* explanation \w for|strong="H1768"\w* \w your|strong="H1768"\w* enemies,” Daniel replied.
\v 20 “\w The|strong="H5922"\w* tree \w you|strong="H1768"\w* \w saw|strong="H2370"\w* \w was|strong="H4430"\w* growing strong \w and|strong="H4430"\w* tall, reaching high into \w the|strong="H5922"\w* \w sky|strong="H8065"\w* \w so|strong="H1768"\w* \w it|strong="H5922"\w* \w could|strong="H1768"\w* \w be|strong="H5732"\w* \w seen|strong="H2370"\w* \w by|strong="H5974"\w* everyone \w in|strong="H5922"\w* \w the|strong="H5922"\w* whole world.
\v 21 \w Its|strong="H6591"\w* leaves \w were|strong="H1768"\w* beautiful, \w and|strong="H4430"\w* \w it|strong="H1932"\w* \w was|strong="H4430"\w* full \w of|strong="H4430"\w* fruit \w for|strong="H5922"\w* all \w to|strong="H5922"\w* eat. Wild animals lived under \w its|strong="H6591"\w* shade, \w and|strong="H4430"\w* birds nested \w in|strong="H5922"\w* \w its|strong="H6591"\w* branches.
\v 22 \w This|strong="H4481"\w* \w is|strong="H1768"\w* \w you|strong="H1768"\w*, \w Your|strong="H1768"\w* Majesty. \w You|strong="H1768"\w* \w have|strong="H1934"\w* grown strong, \w your|strong="H1768"\w* power \w has|strong="H1768"\w* become \w so|strong="H1768"\w* great \w that|strong="H1768"\w* \w it|strong="H5922"\w* \w has|strong="H1768"\w* reached \w high|strong="H5943"\w* into \w the|strong="H5922"\w* \w sky|strong="H8065"\w*, \w and|strong="H4437"\w* \w your|strong="H1768"\w* \w rule|strong="H7990"\w* extends \w to|strong="H5922"\w* \w the|strong="H5922"\w* ends \w of|strong="H4481"\w* \w the|strong="H5922"\w* earth.
\p 
\v 23 \w Then|strong="H1768"\w* \w Your|strong="H1768"\w* Majesty saw \w a|strong="H3068"\w* watcher, \w a|strong="H3068"\w* holy one, coming down \w from|strong="H4481"\w* \w heaven|strong="H8065"\w* \w who|strong="H1768"\w* said, ‘Cut down \w the|strong="H4481"\w* tree \w and|strong="H4437"\w* destroy \w it|strong="H4481"\w*, \w but|strong="H1768"\w* \w leave|strong="H7662"\w* \w the|strong="H4481"\w* \w stump|strong="H6136"\w* \w and|strong="H4437"\w* \w its|strong="H3046"\w* \w roots|strong="H8330"\w* \w in|strong="H4437"\w* \w the|strong="H4481"\w* ground, \w and|strong="H4437"\w* bind \w it|strong="H4481"\w* with iron \w and|strong="H4437"\w* bronze, surrounded \w by|strong="H4481"\w* \w the|strong="H4481"\w* new grass \w of|strong="H4481"\w* \w the|strong="H4481"\w* field. Let \w him|strong="H4481"\w* become soaked with \w the|strong="H4481"\w* dew \w of|strong="H4481"\w* \w heaven|strong="H8065"\w* \w and|strong="H4437"\w* let \w him|strong="H4481"\w* live with \w the|strong="H4481"\w* animals outside \w in|strong="H4437"\w* \w the|strong="H4481"\w* undergrowth. Let \w his|strong="H4481"\w* mind become like \w that|strong="H1768"\w* \w of|strong="H4481"\w* \w an|strong="H4437"\w* animal. Let \w him|strong="H4481"\w* be like \w this|strong="H4481"\w* \w for|strong="H1768"\w* seven times.’
\p 
\v 24 \w This|strong="H5922"\w* is what \w it|strong="H5922"\w* means, \w Your|strong="H5922"\w* Majesty, \w and|strong="H4430"\w* what \w the|strong="H5922"\w* Most High \w has|strong="H4430"\w* decreed \w will|strong="H4430"\w* happen \w to|strong="H5922"\w* \w my|strong="H5922"\w* lord \w the|strong="H5922"\w* \w king|strong="H4430"\w*.
\v 25 \w You|strong="H5922"\w* \w will|strong="H4430"\w* be driven away from human society \w and|strong="H4430"\w* \w you|strong="H5922"\w* \w will|strong="H4430"\w* live \w with|strong="H5922"\w* \w the|strong="H3606"\w* wild animals. \w You|strong="H5922"\w* \w will|strong="H4430"\w* eat grass like \w the|strong="H3606"\w* cattle, \w and|strong="H4430"\w* \w you|strong="H5922"\w* \w will|strong="H4430"\w* be soaked \w with|strong="H5922"\w* \w the|strong="H3606"\w* dew \w of|strong="H4430"\w* heaven. \w You|strong="H5922"\w* \w will|strong="H4430"\w* be like \w this|strong="H3606"\w* \w for|strong="H5922"\w* seven times until \w you|strong="H5922"\w* acknowledge \w that|strong="H3606"\w* \w the|strong="H3606"\w* Most High rules \w over|strong="H5922"\w* human kingdoms, \w and|strong="H4430"\w* \w that|strong="H3606"\w* \w he|strong="H5020"\w* gives \w them|strong="H5922"\w* \w to|strong="H5922"\w* those \w he|strong="H5020"\w* chooses.
\v 26 However, \w as|strong="H1768"\w* \w it|strong="H5922"\w* \w was|strong="H1934"\w* decreed, \w the|strong="H5922"\w* stump \w and|strong="H4437"\w* its roots \w were|strong="H1934"\w* \w to|strong="H5922"\w* \w be|strong="H1934"\w* left \w in|strong="H5922"\w* \w the|strong="H5922"\w* ground. \w Your|strong="H1768"\w* \w kingdom|strong="H4437"\w* \w will|strong="H1768"\w* \w be|strong="H1934"\w* restored \w to|strong="H5922"\w* \w you|strong="H1768"\w* \w when|strong="H1768"\w* \w you|strong="H1768"\w* acknowledge \w that|strong="H1768"\w* Heaven rules.
\p 
\v 27 \w So|strong="H1768"\w*, \w Your|strong="H1768"\w* \w Majesty|strong="H1923"\w*, please take \w my|strong="H1768"\w* advice. Stop sinning \w and|strong="H6032"\w* do \w what|strong="H1768"\w*'s right. End \w your|strong="H1768"\w* iniquities \w and|strong="H6032"\w* \w be|strong="H3809"\w* merciful \w to|strong="H4430"\w* \w the|strong="H1768"\w* oppressed. Maybe \w then|strong="H4430"\w* things \w will|strong="H1768"\w* continue \w to|strong="H4430"\w* go well \w for|strong="H1768"\w* \w you|strong="H1768"\w*.”
\p 
\v 28 (However, all \w this|strong="H4406"\w* did happen \w to|strong="H5308"\w* \w King|strong="H4430"\w* \w Nebuchadnezzar|strong="H5020"\w*.
\v 29 Twelve months later \w he|strong="H1768"\w* \w was|strong="H2423"\w* walking \w on|strong="H5922"\w* \w the|strong="H5922"\w* roof\f + \fr 4:29 \ft “On the roof”: literally just “on.” Buildings of the time had flat roofs, which would explain why the king was walking “on” the royal palace.\f* \w of|strong="H4481"\w* \w the|strong="H5922"\w* \w royal|strong="H4437"\w* palace \w in|strong="H5922"\w* Babylon.
\v 30 \w He|strong="H1768"\w* said, “\w I|strong="H4481"\w* \w was|strong="H1655"\w* \w the|strong="H5922"\w* one \w who|strong="H1768"\w* built \w this|strong="H4406"\w* \w great|strong="H7236"\w* city \w of|strong="H4481"\w* Babylon! \w By|strong="H4481"\w* \w my|strong="H5922"\w* own \w great|strong="H7236"\w* power \w I|strong="H4481"\w* built \w it|strong="H5922"\w* \w as|strong="H6211"\w* \w my|strong="H5922"\w* royal residence \w for|strong="H5922"\w* \w my|strong="H5922"\w* majestic glory!”
\p 
\v 31 \w The|strong="H5922"\w* words \w were|strong="H1768"\w* still \w on|strong="H5922"\w* \w the|strong="H5922"\w* king's lips \w when|strong="H1768"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* voice \w came|strong="H5020"\w* \w from|strong="H1768"\w* \w heaven|strong="H8065"\w*, “King \w Nebuchadnezzar|strong="H5020"\w*, \w this|strong="H5922"\w* \w is|strong="H1768"\w* \w what|strong="H1768"\w* \w is|strong="H1768"\w* decreed \w concerning|strong="H5922"\w* \w you|strong="H1768"\w*: \w the|strong="H5922"\w* \w kingdom|strong="H4437"\w* \w has|strong="H1768"\w* been \w taken|strong="H7985"\w* away \w from|strong="H1768"\w* \w you|strong="H1768"\w*.
\v 32 \w You|strong="H1768"\w* \w will|strong="H6634"\w* \w be|strong="H3809"\w* driven away \w from|strong="H1768"\w* human society \w and|strong="H8065"\w* \w you|strong="H1768"\w* \w will|strong="H6634"\w* \w live|strong="H1753"\w* \w with|strong="H5648"\w* \w the|strong="H3606"\w* wild animals. \w You|strong="H1768"\w* \w will|strong="H6634"\w* eat grass like \w the|strong="H3606"\w* cattle, \w and|strong="H8065"\w* \w you|strong="H1768"\w* \w will|strong="H6634"\w* become soaked \w with|strong="H5648"\w* \w the|strong="H3606"\w* dew \w of|strong="H1768"\w* \w heaven|strong="H8065"\w*. \w You|strong="H1768"\w* \w will|strong="H6634"\w* \w be|strong="H3809"\w* like \w this|strong="H3606"\w* \w for|strong="H1768"\w* seven times until \w you|strong="H1768"\w* acknowledge \w that|strong="H1768"\w* \w the|strong="H3606"\w* \w Most|strong="H2429"\w* High rules over human kingdoms, \w and|strong="H8065"\w* \w that|strong="H1768"\w* \w he|strong="H1768"\w* gives them \w to|strong="H2429"\w* whoever \w he|strong="H1768"\w* chooses.”
\p 
\v 33 Immediately \w the|strong="H5922"\w* decree \w was|strong="H2122"\w* fulfilled, \w and|strong="H4437"\w* Nebuchadnezzar \w was|strong="H2122"\w* driven away \w from|strong="H3367"\w* human society. He ate grass like \w the|strong="H5922"\w* cattle, \w and|strong="H4437"\w* \w his|strong="H5922"\w* body \w was|strong="H2122"\w* soaked \w with|strong="H5922"\w* \w the|strong="H5922"\w* dew \w of|strong="H4437"\w* heaven. \w His|strong="H5922"\w* hair grew matted like \w a|strong="H3068"\w* vulture, \w and|strong="H4437"\w* \w his|strong="H5922"\w* nails like bird claws.)
\p 
\v 34 Once \w the|strong="H3606"\w* time \w had|strong="H4430"\w* passed, \w I|strong="H1768"\w*, \w Nebuchadnezzar|strong="H5020"\w*, looked \w up|strong="H7313"\w* \w to|strong="H3202"\w* \w heaven|strong="H8065"\w* \w and|strong="H4430"\w* \w my|strong="H1768"\w* sanity returned \w to|strong="H3202"\w* me. \w I|strong="H1768"\w* blessed \w and|strong="H4430"\w* \w praised|strong="H7624"\w* \w the|strong="H3606"\w* Most High \w and|strong="H4430"\w* worshiped \w the|strong="H3606"\w* One \w who|strong="H1768"\w* lives forever. \w His|strong="H3606"\w* rule \w is|strong="H1768"\w* \w an|strong="H4430"\w* eternal rule, \w and|strong="H4430"\w* \w his|strong="H3606"\w* kingdom lasts \w for|strong="H1768"\w* \w all|strong="H3606"\w* generations.
\v 35 Everyone who lives on earth is as nothing compared to him. He does whatever he chooses among the heavenly host and among those who live on earth. No one can hold him back from what he does, or ask him, “What are you doing?”
\p 
\v 36 When my sanity returned, then my kingdom, majesty, and splendor also returned to me. My advisors and nobles came looking for me, and I was restored as ruler over my kingdom, even greater than before.
\p 
\v 37 So now I, Nebuchadnezzar, praise, honor, and glorify the King of Heaven, for everything he does is right, and his ways are true. He is able to humble those who are proud.
\b
\c 5
\p 
\v 1 \w King|strong="H4430"\w* \w Belshazzar|strong="H1113"\w* \w held|strong="H5648"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w great|strong="H7229"\w* \w feast|strong="H3900"\w* \w for|strong="H6903"\w* one thousand \w of|strong="H4430"\w* his \w nobles|strong="H7261"\w*, \w and|strong="H4430"\w* \w he|strong="H6903"\w* \w was|strong="H4430"\w* \w drinking|strong="H8355"\w* \w wine|strong="H2562"\w* \w with|strong="H5648"\w* them.
\v 2 \w Under|strong="H4481"\w* \w the|strong="H4481"\w* \w wine|strong="H2562"\w*'s influence \w Belshazzar|strong="H1113"\w* ordered \w his|strong="H4481"\w* servants \w to|strong="H4481"\w* bring \w in|strong="H5020"\w* \w the|strong="H4481"\w* cups \w and|strong="H4430"\w* bowls \w of|strong="H4481"\w* \w gold|strong="H1722"\w* \w and|strong="H4430"\w* \w silver|strong="H3702"\w* \w his|strong="H4481"\w* father\f + \fr 5:2 \ft “Father” as used here does not necessarily mean his actual father.\f* \w Nebuchadnezzar|strong="H5020"\w* \w had|strong="H4430"\w* \w taken|strong="H5312"\w* \w from|strong="H4481"\w* \w the|strong="H4481"\w* \w Temple|strong="H1965"\w* \w in|strong="H5020"\w* \w Jerusalem|strong="H3390"\w* \w so|strong="H1768"\w* \w that|strong="H1768"\w* \w he|strong="H1768"\w* \w and|strong="H4430"\w* \w his|strong="H4481"\w* \w nobles|strong="H7261"\w*, \w his|strong="H4481"\w* \w wives|strong="H7695"\w* \w and|strong="H4430"\w* \w concubines|strong="H3904"\w*, \w could|strong="H1768"\w* \w drink|strong="H8355"\w* \w from|strong="H4481"\w* them.
\v 3 \w So|strong="H1768"\w* \w they|strong="H1768"\w* \w brought|strong="H5312"\w* \w in|strong="H1965"\w* \w the|strong="H4481"\w* \w gold|strong="H1722"\w* cups \w and|strong="H4430"\w* bowls \w that|strong="H1768"\w* \w had|strong="H4430"\w* been \w taken|strong="H5312"\w* \w from|strong="H4481"\w* \w the|strong="H4481"\w* \w Temple|strong="H1005"\w* \w of|strong="H4481"\w* God \w in|strong="H1965"\w* \w Jerusalem|strong="H3390"\w*. \w The|strong="H4481"\w* \w king|strong="H4430"\w* \w and|strong="H4430"\w* \w his|strong="H4481"\w* \w nobles|strong="H7261"\w*, \w his|strong="H4481"\w* \w wives|strong="H7695"\w* \w and|strong="H4430"\w* \w concubines|strong="H3904"\w*, \w drank|strong="H8355"\w* \w from|strong="H4481"\w* them.
\v 4 As they \w drank|strong="H8355"\w* \w wine|strong="H2562"\w* they \w praised|strong="H7624"\w* their gods—idols made of \w gold|strong="H1722"\w*, \w silver|strong="H3702"\w*, \w bronze|strong="H5174"\w*, \w iron|strong="H6523"\w*, wood, \w and|strong="H6523"\w* stone.
\p 
\v 5 \w Immediately|strong="H8160"\w* \w the|strong="H5922"\w* fingers \w of|strong="H4430"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* human \w hand|strong="H3028"\w* \w appeared|strong="H5312"\w*, \w writing|strong="H3790"\w* \w on|strong="H5922"\w* \w the|strong="H5922"\w* \w plaster|strong="H1528"\w* \w wall|strong="H3797"\w* \w of|strong="H4430"\w* \w the|strong="H5922"\w* \w king|strong="H4430"\w*'s \w palace|strong="H1965"\w*, \w opposite|strong="H6903"\w* \w the|strong="H5922"\w* \w lampstand|strong="H5043"\w*. \w The|strong="H5922"\w* \w king|strong="H4430"\w* watched \w the|strong="H5922"\w* \w hand|strong="H3028"\w* \w as|strong="H6903"\w* \w it|strong="H5922"\w* \w wrote|strong="H3790"\w*.
\v 6 His \w face|strong="H2122"\w* turned \w pale|strong="H8133"\w*,\f + \fr 5:6 \ft “His face turned pale”: literally “his face changed.”\f* \w and|strong="H4430"\w* he became very frightened. His legs gave way \w and|strong="H4430"\w* his knees knocked \w together|strong="H1668"\w*.
\p 
\v 7 \w The|strong="H3606"\w* \w king|strong="H4430"\w* \w shouted|strong="H7123"\w*, “\w Bring|strong="H5954"\w* \w in|strong="H5954"\w* \w the|strong="H3606"\w* enchanters \w and|strong="H6032"\w* astrologers \w and|strong="H6032"\w* \w diviners|strong="H1505"\w*!” \w He|strong="H1768"\w* told \w these|strong="H1836"\w* \w wise|strong="H2445"\w* \w men|strong="H2445"\w* \w of|strong="H4437"\w* Babylon, “\w Anyone|strong="H3606"\w* \w who|strong="H1768"\w* \w can|strong="H1768"\w* \w read|strong="H7123"\w* \w this|strong="H1836"\w* \w writing|strong="H3792"\w* \w and|strong="H6032"\w* explain \w it|strong="H5922"\w* \w to|strong="H5922"\w* \w me|strong="H5922"\w* \w will|strong="H1768"\w* be \w clothed|strong="H3848"\w* \w in|strong="H5954"\w* purple \w and|strong="H6032"\w* \w have|strong="H7981"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w gold|strong="H1722"\w* \w chain|strong="H2002"\w* placed \w around|strong="H5922"\w* \w his|strong="H5922"\w* \w neck|strong="H6676"\w*, \w and|strong="H6032"\w* \w he|strong="H1768"\w* \w will|strong="H1768"\w* become \w the|strong="H3606"\w* \w third|strong="H8523"\w* highest \w ruler|strong="H7981"\w* \w in|strong="H5954"\w* \w the|strong="H3606"\w* \w kingdom|strong="H4437"\w*.”\f + \fr 5:7 \ft “Third highest ruler”: It is believed that Belshazzar was regent for his father Nabonidus, which is why he could only offer third place rather than second place in the kingdom.\f*
\p 
